The evidence with the title 'UNICEF - goal: reduce child mortality ' says Child survival lies at the heart of everything UNICEF does. About 29,000 children under the age of five – 21 each minute – die every day , mainly from preventable causes . More than 70 per cent of almost 11 million child deaths every year are attributable to six causes : diarrhoea, malaria, neonatal infection, pneumonia,  ... 
